Package com.github.suloginscene.algorithmhelper.core.graph

Class Graph<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.suloginscene.algorithmhelper.core.graph.Graph<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - Vertex.
    public abstract class Graph<V>
extends java.lang.Object
    Core abstract class to extend, providing utility methods. It is directed weighted graph. If you want make undirected or unweighted graph, you can override #addEdge(). But I think almost functions work properly in directed weighted graph with validating status.

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge​(@NonNull
                    V from,
                    @NonNull
                    V to,
                    int weight)
        Add edge through validation. Weight should not negative and Edge to itself is not allowed. User can override to make unweighted or undirected graph. Add edge bidirectionally to make undirected graph without overriding is not recommended.
